cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of learning to behave optimally in a Markov Decision Process when a reward function is not specified, but instead, a set of demonstrators of varying performance is available. This problem is a classic topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, and the paper proposes a new approach based on ordinal regression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with the problem of determining passenger-finding strategies for taxi drivers, which suggests a possible connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
